3. Information We Collect
We collect information that you voluntarily provide to us when you use the App. The information we collect includes:
• Addiction type selection (stored locally on your device)
• Awareness count and progress data (stored locally on your device)
• Language preference (stored locally on your device)
• Subscription status (processed through RevenueCat)
4. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:
• Provide personalized grounding exercises based on your selected addiction type
• Track your progress and moments of awareness
• Display the app in your preferred language
• Process subscription purchases
• Improve and optimize our application
5. Data Storage
Most of your personal data is stored locally on your device using secure storage mechanisms. We do not store your personal progress data on our servers. Subscription information is processed securely through RevenueCat, a third-party payment processor.
6. Third-Party Services
We use the following third-party services:
• RevenueCat: For processing in-app subscriptions. RevenueCat's privacy policy can be found at https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy
• OpenAI: For generating personalized grounding questions. No personal identifying information is shared with OpenAI.
• Apple App Store / Google Play Store: For app distribution and payment processing
7. Data Retention
Your local data remains on your device until you delete the app or reset your data within the app. Subscription data is retained by RevenueCat according to their data retention policies.
8. Your Privacy Rights
You have the right to:
• Access your personal data stored locally on your device
• Delete your data by using the reset function in the app or uninstalling the app
• Change your addiction type selection at any time
• Cancel your subscription at any time through the App Store or Google Play Store
9. Children's Privacy
The App is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
10. Security
We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect your personal information. While we have taken reasonable steps to secure the personal information you provide to us, please be aware that no security measures are perfect or impenetrable.
11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
